00:11:05,462 --> 00:11:06,612
Fail of the Week.

89
00:11:06,612 --> 00:11:12,450
$400M Snap-Perplexity: Announced, Never Delivered, Quietly Buried

90
00:11:12,450 --> 00:11:26,012
In November 2025, a $400M partnership between Snap and Perplexity was announced with fanfare: AI search directly into the Snapchat chat interface, cash plus equity over one year .

91
00:11:26,012 --> 00:11:34,500
In Q1 2026, the collaboration ended according to Snap's own statement "amicably" — before any broad rollout occurred.

92
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:39,575
A limited live test ran, but agreement on the broader rollout was never reached .

93
00:11:39,575 --> 00:11:49,212
The official wording from Snap's quarterly report: "amicably ended the relationship in Q1 – sales guidance assumes no contribution from Perplexity" .

94
00:11:49,212 --> 00:11:52,912
No statement on the reasons, no explanation for the failure.

95
00:11:52,912 --> 00:12:00,300
$400M announced, press releases generated, expectations raised — and then: silence.

96
00:12:00,300 --> 00:12:06,100
Why this is a fail: Not the failure of the partnership itself, but the communication around it.

97
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:08,537
Tech partnerships fail — that's normal.

98
00:12:08,537 --> 00:12:16,487
But a $400M announcement with no subsequent transparency about why it ended damages trust in both companies.

99
00:12:16,487 --> 00:12:20,887
Investor relations learns about it as a footnote in the quarterly report.

100
00:12:20,887 --> 00:12:25,000
In 2026, that's not acceptable communication practice.

101
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,137
Number of the Week.

102
00:12:26,137 --> 00:12:27,712
$40,000,000,000

103
00:12:27,712 --> 00:12:32,787
Nvidia's AI equity investments in the first months of 2026 alone .

104
00:12:32,787 --> 00:12:48,825
The breakdown: including $30B in OpenAI, $3.2B in Corning (fiber optics for data centers), $2.1B in IREN (data center operator) — the remainder distributed across two dozen other startups .

105
00:12:48,825 --> 00:12:56,087
Nvidia is no longer merely a chip seller — it's a strategic financial investor financing its own ecosystem.

106
00:12:56,087 --> 00:13:08,162
Analysts like Matthew Bryson of Wedbush Securities warn of what they call "circular capital flows" : Nvidia invests in GPU customers, who use the capital to purchase more Nvidia GPUs.

107
00:13:08,162 --> 00:13:21,912
The counterargument is legitimate: strategic investments in one's own ecosystem are established practice among tech giants — comparable to Apple's or Microsoft's venture programs running alongside massive R&D spending.

108
00:13:21,912 --> 00:13:29,112
The question is not whether this strategy is legitimate, but whether the feedback loop will one day sustain the valuations.

109
00:13:29,112 --> 00:13:31,875
A self-reinforcing loop — until it isn't.

